author: Hardeep Phull
title: Iggy Azalea’s ‘Mo Bounce’ is the best thing she’s done for years | New York Post
text:
Just three years ago, Aussie rapper Iggy Azalea was the biggest name in pop, but her fall from grace has been steep. On Thursday, she released the throbbing club-ready new single “Mo Bounce,” and it’s the best thing the 26-year-old has released since her glory days of 2014.
Here’s how her fluctuating career has played out.
June 2014 – “Fancy”/“Problem” The summer of 2014 saw Iggy at her most ubiquitous. Following her debut album “The New Classic,” “Fancy” featuring Charli XCX hit No. 1 on the Billboard Hot 100 for seven weeks, while her collaboration with Ariana Grande, “Problem,” peaked at No. 2.

October 2014 – “Black Widow” Iggy’s hot streak continued with this Rita Ora duet, which reached No. 3.
January 2015 – “Beg for It” This rushed collaboration with MØ sounded too similar to her hits and stalled at No. 27. The rapper suddenly seemed to be running out of ideas.
May 2015 – “Pretty Girls” After months of hype, Iggy’s duet with Britney Spears turned out to be hugely anticlimactic for fans of both stars, and barely scraped the Top 30.

March 2016 – “Team” Iggy’s big comeback (and first material from her upcoming second album “Digital Distortion”) signaled a more electronic direction, but it proved to be her biggest flop yet, failing to even reach the Top 40.
March 2017 – “Mo Bounce” After taking some time off following her break up with fiancé, NBA star Nick Young, Iggy is trying for another reboot with the ultra-catchy “Mo Bounce.” It might not restore her to her former dominance, but it’s the strong comeback she desperately needs.
